<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-16T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="775" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/33</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-16T17:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1915, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>173. In reference to your telegram of August 10, 11 a.m., number 37,
                                regarding question of Danish West Indies. It is evident that from
                                the necessity of keeping up the popular benevolent institutions and
                                maintaining the <hi rend="italic">quasi</hi> mobilization the Danish
                                Government will soon need money.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>